                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.443,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 58452,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in Dodd versus United States will be announced by Justice O\u0027Connor."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.443,
                        "stop": 247.164,
                        "byte_start": 58452,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15092,
                            "name": "Sandra Day O\u0027Connor",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/sandra_day_oconnor",
                            "last_name": "O\u0027Connor",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2736,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 370242000,
                                    "date_end": 1138687200,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2736"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32763,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49563,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/sandra_day_oconnor.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8894,
                            "identifier": "sandra_day_oconnor"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.443,
                                "stop": 12.556,
                                "byte_start": 58452,
                                "byte_stop": 78932,
                                "text": "This case comes here on writ of certiorari to the Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 12.556,
                                "stop": 15.836,
                                "byte_start": 78932,
                                "byte_stop": 92097,
                                "text": "It is another case about a statute of limitations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.836,
                                "stop": 32.883,
                                "byte_start": 92097,
                                "byte_stop": 160225,
                                "text": "The petitioner, Michael Donald Dodd was convicted in Federal Court of knowingly and intentionally engaging in a continuing criminal enterprise in violation of 21 U.S. Code Sections 841 and 846 along with several other crimes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 32.883,
                                "stop": 38.056,
                                "byte_start": 160225,
                                "byte_stop": 180914,
                                "text": "His conviction became final on August 6th, 1997."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 38.056,
                                "stop": 51.494,
                                "byte_start": 180914,
                                "byte_stop": 234726,
                                "text": "More than three years later, in April 2001, Dodd filed a pro se motion for writ of habeas corpus under 28 U.S. Code 2255."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.494,
                                "stop": 62.741,
                                "byte_start": 234726,
                                "byte_stop": 279656,
                                "text": "He sought to set aside his conviction based on an intervening decision of this Court in a case called Richardson versus United States."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 62.741,
                                "stop": 92.307,
                                "byte_start": 279656,
                                "byte_stop": 397939,
                                "text": "Dodd tried to take advantage of the one year statute of limitations in a subsection of Section 2255 which provides that the one year limitation period begins to run on the date on which the right asserted was initially recognized by the Supreme Court, if that right has been newly recognized by the Supreme Court and made retroactively applicable to cases on collateral review."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.307,
                                "stop": 108.94,
                                "byte_start": 397939,
                                "byte_stop": 464499,
                                "text": "Dodd argued that that limitation period did not begin to run until April 2002 when the Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit held that the right recognized in Richardson applied retroactively to cases on collateral review."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 108.94,
                                "stop": 121.744,
                                "byte_start": 464499,
                                "byte_stop": 515699,
                                "text": "The Federal District Court dismissed Dodd\u0027s motion for habeas as time barred because the Richardson case had been decided more than one year before Dodd filed his motion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 121.744,
                                "stop": 124.842,
                                "byte_start": 515699,
                                "byte_stop": 528133,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 124.842,
                                "stop": 131.823,
                                "byte_start": 528133,
                                "byte_stop": 556032,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the Clerk of the Court today, we affirm the Eleventh Circuit\u0027s judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.823,
                                "stop": 143.937,
                                "byte_start": 556032,
                                "byte_stop": 604515,
                                "text": "We hold that the text of paragraph 6.3 unequivocally identifies one and only one date from which the one year limitation period is measured."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.937,
                                "stop": 150.589,
                                "byte_start": 604515,
                                "byte_stop": 631056,
                                "text": "The statute says the date on which the right asserted was initially recognized by the Supreme Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 150.589,
                                "stop": 157.035,
                                "byte_start": 631056,
                                "byte_stop": 656865,
                                "text": "The second clause of the paragraph has no impact on the date identified in the first clause."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.035,
                                "stop": 173.22,
                                "byte_start": 656865,
                                "byte_stop": 721648,
                                "text": "It limits the paragraphs application to cases in which applicants are seeking to assert rights newly recognized by the Supreme Court made retroactively applicable to cases on collateral review."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.22,
                                "stop": 190.031,
                                "byte_start": 721648,
                                "byte_stop": 788835,
                                "text": "That means that if this Court decides a case recognizing a new right, a federal prisoner seeking to assert that right will have one year from the date of this Court\u0027s decision for judgment within which to file his Section 2255 motion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 190.031,
                                "stop": 198.7,
                                "byte_start": 788835,
                                "byte_stop": 823526,
                                "text": "He may take advantage of the date in the first clause of paragraph 6.3 only if the conditions in the second clause are met."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 198.7,
                                "stop": 212.101,
                                "byte_start": 823526,
                                "byte_stop": 877129,
                                "text": "Now, in this case, Dodd\u0027s motion sought to benefit from our holding in Richardson which was decided June 1, 1999 so he had one year from that date within which to file his motion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 212.101,
                                "stop": 218.164,
                                "byte_start": 877129,
                                "byte_stop": 901371,
                                "text": "Because he did not file it until April, 2001, the motion was untimely."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 218.164,
                                "stop": 247.164,
                                "byte_start": 901371,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed a dissenting opinion which Justices Souter, Ginsburg and Breyer join in part; Justice Ginsburg has filed a dissenting opinion which just Justice Breyer has joined."
                            }
                        ]
